div.div:
Refactor code in Invoice.php and adjust product reference
The unnecessary classes named 'Accounting', 'AccountingDocument', and 'ShopCustomer' from the Console Commands Invoice.php file have been removed. Also, in the product retrieval loop, the product reference is now based on the 'product_id' attribute, which replaces the previous direct reference to 'id', ensuring consistency across different parts of the application.

Add new InvoiceList layout and update invoice id reference
The new InvoiceList layout has been added under Orchid\Layouts. The implementation includes the display of actions, order and invoice IDs, and the creation time of invoices. The term 'invoice_id' has been replaced with 'report_id' across invoice-related classes, following a naming convention change. This involved modifications in the order_invoice table migration, Invoice console command, and ReportController.

Update invoice view layout and style
This commit represents a significant overhaul of the invoice.blade.php file. Not only was nearly every line of code in this file altered, but extensive in-line CSS was also added. Major changes include the addition of a new style for the page, a change to the author meta tag, and numerous changes to the structure and styling of the invoice details. All this aims to enhance the look and feel of the invoice generated, resulting in a more professional and sleek design.

Add invoice generation functionality and modify various UI inputs
Implemented a new `Invoice` command and migration for `order_invoice`. This implementation introduces functionality to generate custom invoices for orders. It handles information like the orderId, unique invoice Id, carrier details and calculates tax & discount info for products. Additionally, various UI inputs have been modified across the application to make them required, improving the integrity of form data. Several fields have also been updated with more accurate placeholder text or help messages. Lastly, a new `Encryption` utility class is added to handle custom encryption needs.

Update return value in isVouchersEnabled method
Switched the return value in isVouchersEnabled method in PlatformProvider from 'shop_sales' to 'shop_vouchers'. This change makes the return value more accurately reflect the method's purpose.
